<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 29 at 11:56AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Lewis
and Clark and southwestern Teton Counties through 1230 PM MDT...
At 1155 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 23
miles west of Augusta moving north at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern Lewis
and Clark and southwestern Teton Counties.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
